{"TopicId":179164,"ForumId":21,"TopicTitle":"Tug module design","CreatedByName":"Jonda","CreatedById":192075,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-21T16:32:03Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jonda","CreatedById":192075,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-21T16:32:03Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi, Im just curious on how to make an efficent tug module for a spade station as when i attach to a part and use the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003Ercs\u003C/abbr\u003E to move\u00A0it will swing to the right or left is there anyway to fix this?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AVaughan","CreatedById":152784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-21T16:54:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt sounds like your engines aren\u0027t thrusting through the center of mass.\u00A0 (Reaction wheels can compensate for small imbalances, but in general you want to make sure that engines are arranged so that the net thrust is\u00A0through the center of mass).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DerekL1963","CreatedById":57091,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-21T17:54:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223472653\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179164\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540140891\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022152784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AVaughan\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n58 minutes ago, AVaughan said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt sounds like your engines aren\u0027t thrusting through the center of mass.\u00A0 (Reaction wheels can compensate for small imbalances, but in general you want to make sure that engines are arranged so that the net thrust is\u00A0through the center of mass).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nAnother trick is to set your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E for translation-only, and use \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E to keep yourself parallel to your target.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThis mod will help ensure your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E is balanced:\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4215346589\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/166546-15-rcs-build-aid-continued-new-dependencies/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:225px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jonda","CreatedById":192075,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-21T18:53:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do u make is so your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003Esas\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0is parallel?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-10-21T18:53:24Z\u0022 title=\u002210/21/2018 06:53  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00225 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 21, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Jonda\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"maallaard","CreatedById":169095,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-21T19:09:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223472728\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179164\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540147980\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022192075\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jonda\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, Jonda said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do u make is so your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003Esas\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0is parallel?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nhow long have you been playing ksp?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-21T19:24:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is going to end up being people sharing their tug designs, and so the thread has been moved to the craft exchange subforum. For example, here\u0027s mine.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/DlKuB4y.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 alt=\u0022DlKuB4y.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNotice the forward part of thrusters on spars to be closer to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E of the module being moved.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-21T19:27:55Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf I\u0027m not mistaken, there\u0027s a mod with adjustable arms that automatically get the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECoM\u003C/abbr\u003E centered between your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E ports.\u00A0 Which one is escaping me however.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy solution (which ended up being more fun anyway) was to stick \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E ports on the payload, and then remove them with \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Inventory System (mod)\u0022\u003EKIS\u003C/abbr\u003E/\u003Cabbr title=\u0022Kerbal Attachment System (mod)\u0022\u003EKAS\u003C/abbr\u003E on EVA after docking.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jonda","CreatedById":192075,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-22T01:11:17Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223472748\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179164\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540149880\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002227914\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vanamonde\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, Vanamonde said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis is going to end up being people sharing their tug designs, and so the thread has been moved to the craft exchange subforum. For example, here\u0027s mine.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/DlKuB4y.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022DlKuB4y.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/DlKuB4y.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNotice the forward part of thrusters on spars to be closer to the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Center of Mass\u0022\u003ECOM\u003C/abbr\u003E of the module being moved.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy guy you are a genius\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheGuyNamedAlan","CreatedById":162058,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-10-22T03:37:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223472728\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022179164\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221540147980\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022192075\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jonda\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Jonda said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHow do u make is so your \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003Esas\u003C/abbr\u003E\u00A0is parallel?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/192075-jonda/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022192075\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/192075-jonda/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Jonda\u003C/a\u003E\u00A0there\u0027s great tutorials on youtube by scott manley and other people who\u0027ll help you. i suggest you get the basic of the game (orbiting, rendezvous, docking and interplanetary stuff before you attempt these more complex structures. Having a good foundation of knowledge is they key to expanding to other, more complex stuff like this.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}